

ğŸ“„ BattleStats Class Documentation

Overview

The BattleStats class is a performance-tracking component used to collect, store, and display important statistical data throughout a battle in Cock Clashers: Object-Oriented Coliseum.
It records metrics such as damage dealt, damage taken, number of skills used, turns played, and critical hits.

This class functions as an analytical tool, allowing both the game system and the player to review battle performance after each match.


---

Purpose

The primary purpose of the BattleStats class is to:

Track player and enemy performance in real time

Provide quantitative feedback after the battle ends

Support features like score systems, leveling, or achievements in future expansions


It enhances post-game evaluation and supports further gameplay balancing.


---

System Role

BattleStats is part of the Model Layer, storing numerical data related to combat performance.
It is used by both:

BattleGame â†’ for recording actions each turn

View Components (via displayStats()) â†’ for presenting results



---

Attributes and Their Meaning

Attribute	Description

totalDamageDealt	Total amount of damage this rooster inflicted on the opponent
totalDamageTaken	Total amount of damage received from the opponent
skillsUsed	Number of skills executed during the battle
turnsPlayed	Total number of turns taken in the combat
criticalHits	Number of critical hits performed



